The draft payments table contains payments in draft status. These are payments that have not started the payments
lifecycle and has not been sent for authorization. They are payments saved by the creator with the intention of being
edited at another time. Draft payments can be as incomplete as the creator makes it since it has not been sent for
Only the creator of the payment is able to access and view their own drafted payments. Drafted payments will not
appear in the Recipient Payment History page. All drafted payments will be displayed on the screen (no lazy loading
or ‘view more’ links necessary). The draft payments table is ordered by descending order with the most recent
drafted payment date at the top of the table.
The complete payments table contains payments in Processing, Completed, Declined, or Cancelled/Rejected status.
All payments in this table are at the end of the payment’s lifecycle and cannot be further actioned by any user. This
table will utilize lazy load/infinite scroll. This is where X values will appear by default, and when the user scrolls down
X more values will be loaded; this will repeat until the user scrolls enough to load all payment values.
This table is ordered in descending order based on date, starting with the newest payment to the oldest. This is so
the user can always see the most recent decisions made on the latest payment.
On the left side of each row users have the ability to select multiple rows to bring up a action bar pinned to the
bottom of the page with actions they can take on their selections. The actions they can take are contextual to the

The payments tables are split up into three separate tables (draft, pending and complete) so a user is quickly able to
navigate between payments based on their status. When there are no payments for a given section a message will display
under that table header, see Skeleton Progress Indicator and Empty Table page for more details.
Sort is always applied to tables; icons appear over all columns when hovering over a table’s header.

The pending payments table contains payments in Approval Required, Approval Pending, and Sent Back status.
This table contains payments that require further action either by the user or other users in the OU. All pending
payments will be displayed on the screen (no lazy loading or ‘view more’ links necessary).
The table is ordered in ascending order based on date, starting with the oldest payment to the newest payment so
the user can focus on the authorization of older payments and make a decision on those payments before the new
Payments with Approval Required status requires the action (approve or decline) of the user. The user will only see
this status if they have authorization to action the payment. Any payments with this status will have a dropdown with
the options to approve and decline the payment as quick links.
Payments with Approval Pending status does not required any action from the user. These payments can be viewed
as a read-only when user clicks on the line item for the payment details. They cannot approve/decline or edit this
payment (unless they are the payment creator).
There is no dropdown options for payments with Approval Pending status.
Payments with Sent Back status are payments that have been declined by the authorizer and returned to the
creator. These payments require the user to make edits to the payment before resending it for authorization.
Payments that have been returned by the authorizer can be left not actioned by the creator if they choose to. Any
payments left in the Sent Back status for XX days will be automatically cancelled by the system.
